Normal and abnormal physiology of swallowing. Etiology, symptoms, assessment and therapy of swallowing disorders.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give theoretical overview of normal/ abnormal physiology of swallowing and provide theoretical knowledge in the etiology, symptoms, assessment and therapy of swallowing disorders.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows the etiology of swallowing disorders (dysphagia).  He/she describes and recognizes symptoms of swallowing disorders and knows assessment methods of swallowing disorders. The student knows the principles of the therapy of swallowing disorders.
